So, solving the mystery of the west passage will open this
door, huh.
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[0]Solving puzzles is such a hassle... *glances around*

...I think it's better to have a collaborator, so I suggest
we solve the puzzle honestly and open it, but what will you
do?
Solve the puzzle and open it!
I think that's a good idea!
Are you really okay with that?
I think that's a good idea!

We don't have time to relax... Can't be helped...
Researcher-san... I'm sorry...
It seems there are no traps in this area.
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]If I go any further, I'll probably get noticed...
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]If I go any further, I'll probably get noticed...
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]There are a bunch of people armed to the teeth!

I've been tampering with the surveillance system, but...
with this much activity, we're bound to raise suspicion...
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[1]Should we just knock them all out?

It's too dangerous to take on so many armed soldiers... If
we can avoid fighting, that would be better.
I checked this floor in the control room earlier...

If we use the corridors on the west side, I think we can get
out to the north.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]If we go any further, we'll probably get noticed...
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]If I go any further, I'll probably be noticed...

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[1]Eh!? What do you mean who am I! Yes, I'm the weird magical
girl!

Could it be you? The "intruder" everyone's been fussing
about since a while ago.

As long as you don't interfere with my research, I don't
really care...

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[1]Um, I won't get in the way, so I'd be happy if you could let
me through here.

Unfortunately, this door is broken at the moment. We're in
the middle of fixing it.

If you want to get out on the north side, please go through
the passage to the east.

Unfortunately, the door here is currently out of order.
We're in the middle of fixing it.

If you want to get to the north side, please go through the
passage to the east.

It seems you've managed to solve the mystery despite being
on guard. It looks like your abilities are the real deal.
As promised, I'll cooperate with the investigation.

This is urgent information. The Guard Drone ahead is
equipped with a \C[2]Spirit Power Reflector\C[0] that I
developed. Once deployed, it will \C[2]reflect all attacks
using spirit power\C[0].
So, I'll give this to you.

This device forcibly stops the operation of the Spirit Power
Reflector. With this, you can attack with magic without it
being reflected.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]But if that's the case, isn't there a device that can
forcibly stop the Drone itself?

The Drone is there for security purposes. With a
researcher's authority, I can't stop its operation
completely.

We're also trapped here. I want you to defeat the Drone and
open the way to the first floor.
I'm counting on you, Amagawa Kohane-chan.
I'm counting on you, Amagawa Kohane-chan.
